{"title": "The Game Never Stopped", "content": "A group of characters take part in a game, for example, a murder mystery role playing game, then someone is apparently Killed Off for Real. One of the characters gets accused of the \"real\" murder, there is much sleuthing, then the truth is revealed \u2014 The Game Never Stopped.\n\nNamed after a quote from the Saved by the Bell episode \"Mystery Weekend\", where such an event was the entire plot.\n\nA Sub-Trope Of False Crucible. Reverse it and you have And You Thought It Was a Game. Another common inversion involves one or more characters who think themselves Genre Savvy enough to spot this trope refusing to believe an actual death has occurred.\n\nNot related to The Game, which you just lost. (Though it is related to The Game, as noted below!)\n\nKeep in mind that the titles alone in the following examples may constitute spoilers.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheGameNeverStopped", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/SavedByTheBell", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheGame", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/HaruhiSuzumiya", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DetectiveConan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/GlassMask", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DetectiveSchoolQ", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/BlackButler", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Pokemon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheGame", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AprilFoolsDay", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/EXistenZ", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheCube", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/CryWolf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Inception", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/KingsmanTheSecretService", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/FearInc", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TedDekker", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ApprenticeAdept", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheGoldenGirls", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheJeffersons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Monk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StargateSG1", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekTheNextGeneration", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/RedDwarf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/Derren